omb, Frances Dorothy. ''Anglophobia in France, 1763\u20131789: an essay in the history of constitutionalism and nationalism'' (Duke University Press, 1950).\n* Andrew, Christopher, \"France and the Making of the Entente Cordiale\" ''Historical Journal'' 10#1 (1967), pp 89\u2013105.\n* Andrews, Stuart. ''The British periodical press and the French Revolution, 1789\u201399'' (Macmillan, 2000)\n* Baugh, Daniel A. ''The Global Seven Years' War, 1754\u20131763: Britain and France in a Great Power Contest'' (Longman, 2011)\n* Black, Jeremy. ''Natural and Necessary Enemies: Anglo-French Relations in the Eighteenth Century'' (1986).\n* Blockley, John Edward. \"Cross Channel Reflections: French Perceptions of Britain from Fashoda to the Boer War\" (PhD dissertation Queen Mary University of London, 2015). [https://qmro.qmul.ac.uk/xmlui/bitstream/handle/123456789/12574/Blockley_John_PhD_Final_211015.pdf?sequence=1 online]\n* Brogan, D. W. ''France under the Republic: The Development of Modern France (1870\u20131939)'' (1941), Scholarly history by a British expert; 764pp. [https://www.questia.com/library/504313/france-under-the-republic-the-development-of-modern online]\n* Brown, David. \"Palmerston and Anglo\u2013French Relations, 1846\u20131865.\" ''Diplomacy and Statecraft'' 17.4 (2006): 675\u2013692.\n* Carroll, E. Malcolm. ''French Public Opinion and Foreign Affairs, 1870\u20131914'' (1931) [https://www.questia.com/library/1226343/french-public-opinion-and-foreign-affairs-1870-1914 online]\n* Cameron-Ash, M. ''Lying for the Admiralty: Captain Cook's Endeavour Voyage'', 2018, Rosenberg Publishing, Sydney,{{ISBN|9780648043966}}\n* Clark, Christopher. ''The sleepwalkers: how Europe went to war in 1914'' (2012)\n* [[Fran\u00e7ois Crouzet|Crouzet, Fran\u00e7ois]]. ''Britain Ascendant. Comparative Studies in Franco-British Economic History'' (Cambridge University Press, 1990).\n* Davis, Richard. ''Anglo-French relations before the Second World War: appeasement and crisis'' (Spri